  <static seed="10" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/PolynomialMultiplication/PolynomialMultiplication5.pg">
    <statement><p>Multiply the polynomials.</p>
<p><m>{2x}\left({-10x+8}\right)=</m><fillin characters="16" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-20x^{2}+16x</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We multiply the monomial by each term in the binomial, using 
the properties of exponents to help us.  <me>\begin{aligned}
              {2x}({-10x+8})\amp ={-20x^{2}+16x}
      \end{aligned}</me></p>
</solution>
